<html lang="en">
  <head>
    <meta charset="utf-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1">

    <link href="https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/npm/bootstrap@5.0.2/dist/css/bootstrap.min.css" rel="stylesheet" integrity="sha384-EVSTQN3/azprG1Anm3QDgpJLIm9Nao0Yz1ztcQTwFspd3yD65VohhpuuCOmLASjC" crossorigin="anonymous">

    <title>LSML Project</title>
  </head>
  <body>
    <div class="container mt-5">
      <div class="alert alert-info" role="alert">
        This project is devoted to the question-answering task. The models are trained using the BoolQ dataset from SuperGLUE.
        The goal is to predict yes/no answer depending on passage and question. After a set of experiments Random Forest 
        classifier gives good accuracy without using GPU.
      </div>
      <form>
        <div class="mb-3">
          <label for="passage" class="form-label">Passage</label>
          <textarea class="form-control" id="passage" name="passage" rows="5">Persian language -- Persian (/ˈpɜːrʒən, -ʃən/), also known by its endonym Farsi (فارسی fārsi (fɒːɾˈsiː) ( listen)), is one of the Western Iranian languages within the Indo-Iranian branch of the Indo-European language family. It is primarily spoken in Iran, Afghanistan (officially known as Dari since 1958), and Tajikistan (officially known as Tajiki since the Soviet era), and some other regions which historically were Persianate societies and considered part of Greater Iran. It is written in the Persian alphabet, a modified variant of the Arabic script, which itself evolved from the Aramaic alphabet.</textarea>
          <div class="form-text">Write custom passage</div>
        </div>
        <div class="mb-3">
          <label for="question" class="form-label">Question</label>
          <input type="text" class="form-control" id="question" name="question" value="Do iran and afghanistan speak the same language">
          <div class="form-text">Write custom question</div>
        </div>
        <button type="button" class="btn btn-primary" id="predict-answer-button">Predict answer</button>
      </form>

      <div class="alert alert-secondary d-flex justify-content-center mt-3 d-none" id="spinner">
        <div class="spinner-border" role="status">
          <span class="visually-hidden">Loading...</span>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="alert alert-success d-flex justify-content-center mt-3 d-none" id="answer"></div>

    </div>
    
